browseSorts.description: The 'Featured' picks are chosen specifically for you by the StockX team.
The 'Most Popular' are the products with the most sales over the past 72 hours.
The 'New Lowest Asks' are the products with the most recently listed Lowest Asks. These are the products that people are ready to sell.
The 'New Highest Bids' are the products with the most recently listed Highest Bids. These are the products that people are ready to buy.
The average sales price over the past twelve months. We've removed fakes, outliers and auctions with multiple listings.
The total number of items sold over the past 12 months. We've removed fakes, outliers and auctions with multiple listings.
A measure of how much price fluctuates. It is calculated as standard deviation divided by average price. A $200 product with 40% volatility results in an average price range of $120 to $280.

A measure of how much more a new, unworn item currently sells for, as compared to its original retail price. An item with a Price Premium of 100% means that the average price of that item right now sells for twice as much as its original retail price.
The last price this product was sold for.
The lowest price someone is currently selling this product for.
The highest price someone is currently offering to pay for this product.

node.name: Photon Dust (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (Women's)
node.description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (W) is made of white leather with Photon Dust leather overlays and Swooshes. A woven Nike label on the tongue and embroidered Nike branding completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (W) released in May of 2021 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Grey Fog
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog features a white leather upper with Grey Fog leather overlays and Swooshes. From there, a matching woven tongue label, heel tab, and sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog released in September of 2021 and retailed for $100.

node.name: White Black Panda
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda
node.description:
From the school-spirited College Colors Program to the vibrant Nike CO.JP collection, Nike Dunks have seen many colorways since the design’s inception in 1985. But with each new colorway, the Dunk’s classic color-blocking has remained in some capacity. Nike put its timeless color-blocking to work with the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black.

The upper Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black is constructed of white leather with black leather overlays and Swooshes. Classic Nike branding is featured on the nylon tongue, nodding to traditional Dunk design elements. A white midsole and black outsole complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black released in January of 2021 and retailed for $100.

To shop all Nike Dunks, click here.

node.name: Cacao Wow (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Cacao Wow (Women's)
node.description:
Nike did it again on July 28, 2023, when they dropped the Dunk Low in the enticing Cacao Wow colorway. This shoe is a surefire hit for those who crave unique kicks.

Crafted with buttery smooth leather, the upper sports a cool Cacao Wow finish, delivering a potent mix of style and comfort. This Dunk Low uses a light, creamy hue for contrast, adding just the right amount of pop.The Cacao Wow Dunk Low is set to turn heads and start conversations

This Nike Dunk in the Cacao Wow colorway was released on July 28, 2023, coming in at a retail price of $110.

node.name: Polar Blue
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Polar Blue
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low in Polar Blue is a unique and crisp colorway of the Dunk Low shoes traditionally worn on the basketball court since the mid-1980s. This shoe has seen technological updates since its debut, resulting in this comfortable and visually striking iteration, and has also become an iconic streetwear shoe.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low is constructed with leather uppers and a rubber outsole. The base is white rubber, and Polar Blue overlays line the perforated toebox, the heel, the laces, and the midsole. The Nike Swoosh also appears in Polar Blue on the midsole. The tongue is padded for comfort, and white Nike branding is also visible on the heel.

Our StockX experts believe the standout feature of this sneaker is the Polar Blue overlays on the white leather base. The color makes the shoe appear crisp and clean, allowing for both sports wear and casual wear. The Nike Dunk Low in Polar Blue was released on October 14th, 2023, at a retail price of $115.

node.name: White Black Panda (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (Women's)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low White Black 2021 women’s sneaker features a white and black leather upper with perforations on the toe box. The base of the upper starts with white leather, and black leather wraps around it in an even pattern. A black Nike Swoosh logo adorns either side of the upper and wraps around the ankle to complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low White Black 2021 women’s sneaker released in March of 2021 and retailed for $100.

To shop all Nike Dunks, click here.

node.name: St. John's (2020/2023)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's (2020/2023)
node.description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This St. John's colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

The Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's is composed of a white leather upper with red leather overlays. A white midsole, red outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in June of 2020 and retailed for $100 and again in October of 2023 and retailed for $110.

node.name: White Black Panda (GS)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (GS)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS) silhouette comes in a stark black and white colorway and is made from premium leather materials throughout. Additionally, white Nike lettering complements the rear ankle support of the silhouette while the Nike Air text along with the customary company Swoosh logo adorns the tongue. In keeping with the color scheme, a white midsole resting atop a black outsole rounds out the look of this Dunk Low Retro shoe.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS) released in March of 2021 and retailed for $85.

node.name: Triple Pink (GS)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (GS)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink has a full leather build, which makes use of three distinct shades of pink to complete the look. The base has a light shade of pink, with a slightly contrasting pink overlay.

The look is completed by the Nike Swoosh in a bold pink that provides a strong contrast and stands out noticeably on the shoe. In addition to the Swoosh on both sides, the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Grade School) features Nike branding on the sole, heel, tongue, and inner sole. This shoe comes in Grade School (GS) sizing.

The Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Grade School) was released in early June, 2022, at the retail price of $85.

node.name: Diffused Taupe (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's) was released alongside several Dunk Low variations with subdued palettes, including Hemp Sail and Cacao Wow. It pays tribute to iconic Nike basketball shoe silhouettes from the ‘80s while utilizing premium materials.

On this Nike Dunk Low for women the upper is crafted entirely from smooth leather with perforations across the vamp and the Swoosh checked across the side. The use of leather gives the shoe a slightly cushiony appearance that adds a minimal amount of bulk to the silhouette. The Diffused Taupe colorway includes Sail, Plum Eclipse, and Diffused taupe, which presents as an off-white base with taupe accents on the overlays, lace cage, heel tab, and rubber outsole.

Our experts at StockX love the Swoosh detail in Plum Eclipse, which contrasts the light tones found on the rest of the shoe. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's) was released on December 1, 2023, and retailed at $110.

node.name: Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh draws inspiration from the Nike Skateboarding Orange Label collection. However, the grey tone colorway and use of premium materials upgrade the classic low-top silhouette synonymous with Nike SB sneakers.

The grey suede and tumbled leather overlays balance out the clean, white upper and the light brown of the gum sole. The heel tabs, which feature ‘NIKE’ in white stitching, and the soft, cloth liner add additional accents in Light Iron Ore and Smoke Grey. Featuring laces with a reflective, speckled pattern, the lace cage houses a mesh tongue displaying Nike branding.

Something we love about this shoe is the 3M reflective detailing on the grey panel Swoosh. It increases visibility during low lighting and exemplifies the attention to detail found in this Nike Dunk Low variation. The Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh was released on October 3, 2023, and retailed at $115.

node.name: Rose Whisper (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper (Women's)
node.description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper arrives in a classic two-tone color blocked look similar to the original Nike Dunks of the 1980s. This Dunk offers a warm palette primed for the summer weather, with a white and Rose Whisper leather construction. Matching woven tongue labels contribute to the design's retro feel, while an EVA foam sole provides cushioning.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper released in June of 2022 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's) is a low-top sneaker that is part of Nike’s "Next Nature" line. All "Next Nature" shoes are crafted with at least 20 percent recycled material and are part of Nike’s effort to minimize carbon emissions.

This two-toned sneaker for women features a Blue Tint, Cobalt Bliss, Summit White, Volt, and Black colorway that is reminiscent of the sky. The bright Summit White base allows the blue hues on the Swoosh, overlays, lace cage, and outsole to pop. In terms of branding details, the tongue boasts a ‘Nike’ label while ‘NIKE’ is also stitched across the heel.

Something our experts love is the incorporation of the Nike Grind midsole. This speckled midsole is made from recycled shoes from Nike’s Reuse-A-Shoe program and pre-consumer scraps created during manufacturing. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's) was released on September 8, 2023, and retailed at $115.

node.name: Medium Olive (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive (Women's)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive W dresses the archival hoops shoe in traditional two-tone color blocking.

The all-leather upper of this Dunk Low Medium for women by Nike merges a crisp white base with olive green overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. Underpinning the sneaker is a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls that contain a lightweight foam wedge for cushion. Underfoot, the olive rubber outsole includes the brand´s herringbone traction pattern and rounds of the silhouette.

The Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive W was released the 9th of September 2022 and originally retailed at a price of $110.

node.name: Medium Curry
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry
node.description:
Nike added a luxe twist to the Dunk Low with the Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry. The Curry colorway first made its way onto the Nike Dunk Low in 1999 as part of the Nike CO.JP (Concept Japan) collection. Since then, there have been multiple Curry Dunk releases in Nike’s catalog, including the 2003 Nike Dunk High Premium Curry, 2010 Nike Dunk Low VNTG Dark Curry, and now, the Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry.

The upper of the Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry is composed of Sail hairy suede with Medium Curry overlays and a Bone-colored Swoosh. Nike branding is present on its traditional woven tongue tag and Medium Curry heel patch. A Sail nylon tongue, Sail midsole, and Medium Curry outsole complete this retro design.

The Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry released in March of 2021 and retailed for $100.

node.name: White Black Panda (PS)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (PS)
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black PS features an entirely white leather upper with black overlays. The touches of black continue to the Swoosh branding, and the vintage basketball shoe is finished off with a padded collar and nylon mesh tongue, a white midsole, and a black outsole and treading. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black PS was released in March 2021 and originally retailed for $65.

node.name: Athletic Department University Blue
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue arrives in a predominantly Light Smoke Gray upper, with accents of University Blue in the classic low-top silhouette.

The Light Smoke Gray University Blue Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department is constructed with a combination of leather and suede for a premium look and feel. The leather overlays provide durability and support, while the suede panels add texture and style. The shoe features a traditional low-top silhouette with a padded collar for comfort. Nike has incorporated its time-tested technology, including a cushioned insole and a rubber outsole with a classic pivot point tread pattern to ensure both comfort and grip. The sneaker adopts a Light Iron Ore EVA foam midsole to provide cushioning and impact protection. Nike's iconic Swoosh logo is prominently displayed on both sides of the shoe, along with Nike branding on the tongue and heel tab.

Our experts say the Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue’s standout feature is its retro-inspired design, paying homage to the Dunk's rich history in the sneaker world. The sneaker was released on July 25th, 2023, for $110.

node.name: Chicago Split
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split boasts a fierce colorway combo of University Red, Black, Light Silver, and White. This sneaker dropped on July 14, 2023. Challenging conventional aesthetics, this Dunk Low model remixes a classic silhouette with a split color design, creating a bold contrast that demands attention.

The upper features university red and white on the medial and lateral sides respectively, with light silver and black dressing the Swoosh logo lending the design its 'split' distinction. A clean white midsole offset the strong, contrasting colors, and a black and white outsole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split hit the shelves on July 14, 2023, at a retail price of $110.

node.name: Team Gold
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Team Gold
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Team Gold arrives in a white, team gold-wolf grey-white color palette.

The Low Team Gold Nike Dunk adopts a classic silhouette with an upper that is made of leather, which provides durability. The shoe's midsole is constructed from a supportive and cushioning foam material. The sneaker's outsole features a durable rubber material with a textured pattern that provides traction. The shoe features the Nike Swoosh on the lateral sides and "NIKE" branding on the heel.

The Nike Dunk Low Team Gold was released on March 14, 2023, and was sold at a retail price of $110.

node.name: Championship Court Purple
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Championship Court Purple
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple features a white leather upper with Championship Purple overlays and Swooshes. Nike embroidery at the heel pays tribute to the original 1985 design. At the base, a white and purple sole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple releases in May of 2022 and retails for $100.

node.name: Industrial Blue Sashiko
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko
node.description:
Nike is drawing inspiration from Japan, using traditional Sashiko stitching on the 2023 release of the Nike Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko.

Nikes Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko is constructed using denim uppers that feature white contrast stitching across the blue denim paneling. Traditional Japanese Sashiko stitching designs are sewn into the toe box and heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Sashiko features white Nike branding on the tongue and insoles.
The Nike Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko released March 9, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

node.name: Triple Pink (PS)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (PS)
node.description:
Since its first release, the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool)remains one of the high-selling variants of the Nike Dunk Low series.
​
The upper of Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) is constructed with light pink-layered leather featuring darker pink overlays of synthetic leather made from recycled polyester material. The toe box is made of pink perforated leather. Its pull tab, which is embroidered with the symbol of "NIKE," is also constructed using pink synthetic leather. The midsole and outsole of the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) are made of pink and white rubber.
​
Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) was first released on September 13, 2022, at a price of $85.

node.name: Reverse Panda
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda features the Nike Swoosh logo in black on the tongue and also on the heel padding behind the ankle.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda has a clean white color throughout, including the sole, with contrasting touches of black. The shoe also features a lace-up closure style with black laces. The Nike Swoosh is found on both sides, also in black, and these meet behind the ankle and below the white heel padding.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda first debuted in Asia in June, 2022, and then in the UK and Europe in July of 2022 at a retail price of $100.

node.name: Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
node.description:
Constructed of FlyLeather, a leather-like material made up of at least 50% recycled materials, the women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (W) features simple color blocking similar to the original 1985 Nike Dunk. It features a white base with Orewood Brown overlays and Swooshes. From there, a white and grey Air sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $105.

node.name: White Pure Platinum
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum is a low-top counterpart to the classic Dunk High silhouette. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro has an all-leather construction leaving the Swoosh logos, outsole, and branded heel tabs in a Platinum grey tone. The shoe has a low-cut padded collar and a perforated toe box with Nike branding in the woven tongue tag, sock liner, and heel tab. It has a rubber cupsole for traction with stitched sidewall construction and an interior foam wedge for comfort. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum was released on 19th November 2022. Upon its launch, its retail price was $110.

node.name: Light Orewood Brown
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown dons the classic Dunk Low low-top silhouette and features a Light Orewood Brown colorway, creating a warm and earthy aesthetic.

The Light Orewood Brown Nike Dunk Low Premium boasts a subtle ivory tone on its upper, which is crafted from breathable canvas and accented with leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. Nike's branding is tastefully incorporated, adorning both the woven tongue tag and the rear tab. The low-top Dunk Low is set atop a cream-colored cup sole, complete with an internal foam wedge for added comfort, and a rubber outsole providing traction and grip.

Our experts say the Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown colorway is the best feature, with a rich and sophisticated appearance. The Light Orewood Brown hue adds a touch of elegance to the classic Dunk Low silhouette, making it a stylish and versatile choice for people who appreciate a classic design with a contemporary twist. The shoe was released on August 30th, 2023, for $120.

node.name: Midnight Navy University Blue
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue comes in a Midnight Navy and white colorway with University Blue and Laser Orange accents.

The upper of the Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue is made of durable leather, which provides the shoe with both durability. The sneaker sits atop a white midsole and the outsole of the shoe showcases a retro-inspired circular herringbone pattern, perfect for traction and grip. The shoe also features a padded collar and tongue, which ensures that the shoe is comfortable and snug on the feet.

We think that the key feature of the Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue is the perforations on the toe box. The perforations are a design element that serves a functional purpose as well. The holes are strategically placed to allow air to circulate through the shoe, which helps to keep the feet cool and dry during intense physical activity. The shoe was released on July 17th, 2023 at a retail price of $110.

node.name: Clear Jade
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade takes a classic silhouette and dresses it in a two-tone colorway that pops.​
​​
​The Clear Jade Nike Dunk Low-Top features a white leather upper with a perforated toebox for breathability. Clear Jade leather is used for the side panel Nike Swoosh and the overlays surrounding the toebox, eyestays, heel, and collar. The tongue is white with Clear Jade trim, and a white branding patch with Clear Jade Nike branding. The padded sock liner is Clear Jade, and the insole is Clear Jade with white Nike branding. The foam cushion midsole is fully sewn-in and sits atop a rubber cup sole. The outsole is Clear Jade rubber with a traction pattern in concentric circles.​
​
​The detail that our sneaker experts appreciate most about this sports shoe is the white embroidery that makes up the Nike branding on the Clear Jade heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade was released on July 1st, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

node.name: LeBron James Fruity Pebbles
node.title: Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles come in Habanero Red mixed with Laser Blue and White colorway.

This Dunk Low sneaker by Nike features a smooth white leather base contrasted with habanero red overlays and a laser blue dressed side Swoosh. The shoe’s white tongue is decorated with the woven Fruity Pebbles tags, while the heel tab is embroidered with LeBron’s LJ logo. The interior part of the sneaker is a Nike-branded sock liner revealing another Fruity Pebble graphic print. Concluding the design is the treaded milky translucent rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles was released in November 2022 and retailed at $120.

node.name: Mica Green
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Mica Green
node.description:
Nike is adding the recently popular Mica Green colorway to part of its Spring/Summer 2023 collection, with the addition of the Nike Dunk Low Mica Green.

The Nike Dunk Low Mica Green is constructed using a Photon Dust canvas and Mica Green leather uppers. Nike used a sail midsole to help give the sneaker a vintage inspired look, and used Mica Green laces to sit over the matching colored tongue.

The Nike Dunk Low Mica Green released May 16, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

node.name: Athletic Department Deep Jungle
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle launched as part of the Nike Athletic Department Pack, which brings old-school styling to fan-favorite Nike models. This sneaker follows the Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue; however, it includes a different nostalgic colorway inspired by varsity sports.

The "Deep Jungle" colorway includes Sail, Deep Jungle, Coconut Milk, and White, which presents as a white base with dark green details. The smooth leather upper comes in Coconut Milk, which contrasts the Deep Jungle found on the suede Swooshes, inner liner, heel tab, and rubber outsole. The sneaker boasts minimal branding, including ‘NIKE’ stitched across the heel tab and the Nike label on the tongue.

Something our experts love is the off-white color of the midsole, which gives the sneaker a worn-in, vintage appearance. The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle was released on October 1, 2023, and retailed at $110.

node.name: Light Orewood Brown Sashiko
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Light Orewood Brown Sashiko
node.description:
Nike is reintroducing Japanese Sashiko stitching into the popular Nike Dunk Low model, after it was last seen used on the Air Force One silhouette in 2022.

The Nike Dunk Low Orewood Brown Sashiko is constructed with a Pale Ivory denim upper that features Orewood Brown contrast stitching throughout. Nike used red Sashiko style stitching across the toe box, heel tab and eyelets. Red Nike branding is placed subtly on the tongue and insoles.

The Nike Dunk Low Light Orewood Brown Sashiko released March 9, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

node.name: Red Swoosh Panda
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda is dressed in a mix of three major colors: white, university red, and black.
​
​The white accents on the tongue tags and leather overlays contrast with the black leather foundation of this Retro Nike Dunk model. Red heels, Swooshes, as well as a rubber outsole with cushioning technology, are visible in the shoe's design. The white lace closure system, lining, black outsole, and white midsole complete the look.
​
​The Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda made its debut on October 1st, 2022, for a recommended retail price of $110.

node.name: Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh is a low-top sneaker in the Nike Dunk line.

The Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh features Total Orange accenting against a black and white base. The shoe's upper is constructed from leather, which provides durability and comfort. The toebox includes perforated detailing that improves breathability, allowing air to circulate to keep the feet fresh. The midsole is made of hard foam, providing exceptional comfort, support, and shock absorption. A rubber outsole offers adequate traction and stability, providing support and grip to the wearer.

We believe that the distinctive feature of the Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh is the use of mini-Swoosh logos on the toe and tongue. These miniature Swooshes have a unique placement, making them visible only upon close observation of the shoe. The sneaker was released on July 29th, 2023, at a price of $110.

node.name: Valentine's Day (2023)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine's Day (2023)
node.description:
Nike is celebrating Valentine’s Day this year with the release of the Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine’s Day (2023). Nike’s 2023 Valentine’s Day collection consisted of the Dunk Low, Air Trainer 1, Uptempo 96, and Air Force 1 silhouettes.

The Nike Valentine’s Day Dunk Low has a burgundy and sail leather upper with a tumbled pink leather Swoosh. The limited edition sneakers have burgundy outsoles, a mesh sockliner, and is tied off with burgundy shoe laces.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine’s Day (2023) released February 7, 2023 with a retail price of $120.

node.name: Reverse Panda
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda arrives following the classic "Panda" style, with the sneaker achieving a harmonious balance of black and white tones across its low-top silhouette.

The Reverse Panda Nike Dunk Low Jumbo textile base layers sport a predominantly black tone, while the textured leather overlays starkly contrast in Crisp White. These overlays extend to elongated panels on the tongue. The mesh base and padded tongue have a Sleek Black finish, while the leather overlays and Swooshes come to life in bright white. Various accents of contrast stitching in white, including on the standard black laces, add subtle detail. Below, the sole unit undergoes modifications, with added reinforcement at the toe and a distinct traction pattern.

What our experts love about the Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda is its distinctive and innovative design. This sneaker takes the iconic "Panda" color blocking theme and flips it on its head, creating a fresh and captivating twist on a classic. The sneaker debuted for $120 on June 20th, 2023.
